CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, reads: "Cornerstone Laying- Sahara Temple No. 2 Ancient Egyptian Arabic order Noble Mystic Shrine of North and South America recently held the cornerstone laying at new headquarters on Orr Street. Heading the laying was the Most Worshipful Grand Master Thomas Logan of Philadelphia.  Those taking part in ceremonies are left to right, Arthur S. Barnes, Imperial Director of Public Relations: Carl Wilson, Imperial Outer Guard of Dayton, Ohio; Marshall S. Johnson, Imperial High Priest and Prophet; Harry J. Keen, Imperial Deputy of the Desert of Pennsylvania; Taylor Thompson, Illustrator Potentate of Sahara Temple No. 2; Thomas Logan most Worshipable Grand Master of Prince Hall Grand Hall State of Pennsylvania; John H. Hester, Imperial Potentate of Atlantic City, New Jersey; Joseph Givens, Past Imperial Potentate, Ottis Lyone Jr., Deputy Imperial Marshall; Robert Irvin, Imperial Deputy Public Relation of Philadelphia; Rev. Leroy Patrick, Imperial Chaplian; Jamer Washinton, Imperial Organizers of the West."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Shriner members, including: Arthur S. Barnes, Carl Wilson, Marshall S. Johnson, Harry J. Keen, Taylor Thompson, Thomas Logan, John H. Hester, Joseph Givens, Ottis Lyone Jr., Robert Irvin, Rev. Leroy Patrick, and Jamer Washington, gathered around cornerstone for ceremony at new headquarters, Orr Street, another version
